on someone?
- Really?

501
00:31:34,326 --> 00:31:37,193
I'll take the right
side. You take the left.

502
00:31:38,130 --> 00:31:40,914
Very gently.

503
00:31:41,016 --> 00:31:44,651
That's it. Take your time.
He's not going anywhere.

504
00:31:46,021 --> 00:31:47,403
Thank you.

505
00:31:49,141 --> 00:31:52,859
Watch the left corner of his
mouth. You're off center just a bit.

506
00:31:53,928 --> 00:31:57,914
There we go. Careful
around the eyes.

507
00:31:59,017 --> 00:32:01,768
Good. Very good, Dr. Grey.

508
00:32:16,435 --> 00:32:17,629
- Get out.
- No.

509
00:32:17,653 --> 00:32:18,796
- Get out!
- No!

510
00:32:18,820 --> 00:32:21,438
- Richard, get out!
- No!

511
00:32:22,707 --> 00:32:25,875
I've destroyed lives
before. Several, in fact.

512
00:32:25,978 --> 00:32:29,229
Yours is not one of them. I sent the
woman you love out here to help you.

513
00:32:29,331 --> 00:32:33,083
I sent the woman who loves you
out here to bring you back to your life.

514
00:32:33,185 --> 00:32:36,920
If you ruin it with her, that's
on you. I don't accept it.

515
00:32:38,039 --> 00:32:40,640
You're scared, drunk,
don't know which way is up.

516
00:32:40,742 --> 00:32:44,594
You threw a punch at your best friend,
a ring at Meredith, wanna throw me out.

517
00:32:44,696 --> 00:32:46,529
I'm not accepting it!

518
00:32:46,631 --> 00:32:49,632
Because I'm older than you,

519
00:32:49,734 --> 00:32:51,734
and I've been where you are.

520
00:32:51,837 --> 00:32:54,621
You been drunk for a few
days. I was drunk for years.

521
00:32:57,776 --> 00:33:00,043
And I know you're gonna
need at least one friend

522
00:33:00,145 --> 00:33:02,779
when you come out of
that hole you're digging.

523
00:33:06,685 --> 00:33:08,819
I hope you come out of it soon.

524
00:33:12,507 --> 00:33:14,374
I'll be here when you do.

525
00:33:16,344 --> 00:33:18,664
I don't think I
can get her back.

526
00:33:22,017 --> 00:33:23,583
Did you call her?

527
00:33:28,323 --> 00:33:30,806
What am I gonna say?

528
00:33:34,779 --> 00:33:37,147
I had an affair for years.

529
00:33:38,984 --> 00:33:42,018
When Adele found
out, somehow she...

530
00:33:46,158 --> 00:33:48,725
She took me back.

531
00:33:51,896 --> 00:33:54,264
You can make your way back...

532
00:33:55,333 --> 00:33:57,167
from anything.

533
00:33:59,905 --> 00:34:02,605
This is year one
of your residency.

534
00:34:02,708 --> 00:34:05,641
You turn on each other
now, you're not gonna make it.

535
00:34:10,899 --> 00:34:13,316
OK. Here's what's gonna happen.

536
00:34:13,418 --> 00:34:16,731
All of you are going to go find
the sense the good Lord gave you

537
00:34:16,755 --> 00:34:20,941
and never behave like this
within the four walls of this hospital

538
00:34:21,043 --> 00:34:23,443
ever again. You are doctors.

539
00:34:23,545 --> 00:34:27,797
Pierce, get an ice pack and put it on
that oozing, disgusting mess of an eye.

540
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:31,351
And, Steve, go to the pit
and get that unsanitary,

541
00:34:31,453 --> 00:34:34,354
bloody hand
X-rayed and stitched.

542
00:34:34,456 --> 00:34:39,643
And, Megan, you should go to
OB because yes, you are pregnant.

543
00:34:41,346 --> 00:34:43,847
That was very Bailey.

544
00:34:47,219 --> 00:34:51,003
- You ready, Dr. Yang?
- Wait! I'm sorry.

545
00:34:51,105 --> 00:34:53,406
I need one thing from
you before I go under.

546
00:34:53,508 --> 00:34:56,676
I haven't asked for much. You
haven't answered my questions.

547
00:34:56,778 --> 00:34:59,311
I understand you're
busy, but I'm scared.

548
00:34:59,414 --> 00:35:02,916
I don't wanna die. I want to go
on a tour of Russia with my friends.

549
00:35:03,018 --> 00:35:07,887
I may just be a batty old lady to
you, and this may be a silly procedure,

